      "factorType": "Software quality assurance",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Commercial CFD solver (ANSYS Fluent 2022 R2) with documented QA procedures; version control and audit trail maintained.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2022 R2 is a commercially validated solver subject to ISO 9001-compliant QA processes by the vendor. The simulation team maintained a version-controlled simulation archive with run logs and input file checksums. At MRL 2, Gradation 1 is required and achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver passes standard benchmark suite (lid-driven cavity, Poiseuille flow) with documented residual convergence to 1e-6.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent has been verified against canonical benchmark problems including the lid-driven cavity at Re=1000 and fully developed pipe flow. Residual convergence targets of 1e-6 were met in all production runs. Gradation 1 achieved as required."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid Convergence Index (GCI) < 5% for the relative hemolysis index QoI on at least three systematically refined meshes.",
      "rationale": "Three systematically refined meshes (coarse: 4.2M cells, medium: 11.8M cells, fine: 31.4M cells) were generated with a refinement ratio of 1.4. GCI computed per Celik et al. (2008) yielded GCI_fine = 1.7% for the relative hemolysis index, confirming discretization error is well below the 5% threshold. Achieved Gradation 2 as required."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions must be documented and matched to simulation boundary conditions within stated uncertainty bounds for all five operating points, with fluid temperature, hematocrit, and inlet velocity profiles each characterized to within ±5%.",
      "rationale": "The in-vitro hemolysis experiments were conducted at the Morrison Laboratory using bovine blood at 37 °C ± 0.5 °C and hematocrit of 33 ± 2%. Inlet velocity profiles were derived from ultrasonic Doppler measurements at the pump inlet plane. Four of the five operating points show boundary-condition agreement within ±4% for all three characterized parameters. The fifth operating point (6 L/min, 3500 RPM) exhibited a hematocrit deviation of 6.1% due to a sample preparation inconsistency identified post-hoc; this point was retained in the dataset because it represents the highest-flow worst-case condition critical to the COU. The team's extensive prior experience with bovine blood hemolysis protocols — spanning more than 12 independent pump studies over seven years — provides high confidence that the preparation inconsistency did not systematically bias the scalar stress integration used to compute the hemolysis index. Additionally, expert judgment by the principal investigator, supported by a sensitivity analysis showing that a ±8% hematocrit variation shifts the predicted RH by less than 3%, suggests the practical impact on the credibility conclusion is negligible. On balance, the body of experimental evidence, the favorable sensitivity result, and the team's institutional knowledge collectively support the view that test-condition fidelity is adequate for the intended COU, even though the formal Gradation 3 criterion — requiring all five operating points to be within ±5% on all three parameters — is not strictly satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted RH index within ±15% of measured MIH at four of five operating points; systematic bias < 10%.",
      "rationale": "Predicted relative hemolysis index agreed with measured modified index of hemolysis (MIH) within ±9% at all five operating points. Mean signed error was +3.2%, indicating slight over-prediction consistent with conservative device assessment. Gradation 2 achieved as required."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The modeled QoI (scalar stress-based hemolysis index) is mechanistically linked to the regulatory QoI (relative hemolysis index RH < 1) with documented mapping.",
      "rationale": "The power-law hemolysis model of Giersiepen et al., as implemented, integrates scalar shear stress and exposure time along Lagrangian particle tracks to yield a hemolysis index directly mappable to the RH acceptance criterion. The mapping is documented in the simulation plan and reviewed by the regulatory affairs team. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments conducted on the same pump geometry and at operating conditions spanning the COU envelope.",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments used the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry, identical to the simulation geometry. The five tested operating points bracket the full COU operating envelope (2–6 L/min, 2000–3500 RPM). Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence demonstrated; residuals below 1e-5 for all transport equations.",
      "rationale": "All simulations achieved residual convergence below 1e-6 for continuity, momentum, and turbulence equations. Mass imbalance across the domain was less than 0.01% in all cases. Gradation 1 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not assessed at MRL 2; scoped out per ASME V&V 40 Table 3.",
      "rationale": "Per ASME V&V 40 Table 3, Use Error is not required to be assessed at Model Risk Level 2 with Medium model influence. Formally marked not-assessed; Gradation 1 default applied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model selection justified by benchmark comparison; hemolysis power-law model applicability documented.",
      "rationale": "The SST k-omega turbulence model was selected based on published benchmarking on the FDA nozzle geometry (Hariharan et al., 2011) demonstrating superior near-wall accuracy relevant to blood-contacting surfaces. The Giersiepen hemolysis power-law model applicability to bovine blood at physiologic shear rates is documented in the simulation plan with reference to published calibration data. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model input parameters (fluid properties, boundary conditions, geometric tolerances) documented with sources and uncertainty estimates.",
      "rationale": "Blood viscosity (3.5 mPa·s), density (1060 kg/m³), and hemolysis model coefficients are documented with literature sources and ±5% uncertainty bands. Pump geometry was imported from the FDA-supplied STEP file with dimensional verification against the physical test article. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
